  "prompt": "Which is best AMCAT, co-cubes or e-litmus?",
  "response": "Each of these assessment platforms has its strengths, and the \"best\" depends on your specific needs and the companies you're targeting:\n\nAMCAT (Aspiring Minds Computer Adaptive Test):\n- Wide acceptance across multiple industries\n- Tests fundamental skills like logical reasoning, quantitative ability\n- Good for entry-level and fresher positions\n- Comprehensive assessment\n- Widely used by many companies\n\nCoCubes:\n- More focused on technical and programming skills\n- Good for engineering and tech-related roles\n- Provides detailed skill assessment\n- Used by many IT and product companies\n- Strong in computer science and programming evaluation\n\nE-Litmus:\n- Primarily used for technical hiring\n- Strong in programming and coding assessments\n- Popular among IT and software companies\n- Good for testing coding and problem-solving skills\n\nRecommendation:\n1. For overall skill assessment: AMCAT\n2. For technical/programming roles: CoCubes or E-Litmus\n3. Best to take multiple tests to increase job opportunities\n\nTip: Research which platforms are preferred by companies you're interested in, as preference can vary by industry and specific organizations.",
